For our starting acoustic variables, I need to cut it down to start. First, Im removing all of the psychoacoustic_min variables. Ill also remove the THD_freq features. The SII is not designed for environmental sound, so well remove it. The LCeq_LAeq and LA10_LA90 have been producing terrible collinearity issues, so well remove them up front.

Feature selection for overall model

First we need to apply a filter for the repeated features - i.e.determine which of each type of psychoacoustic feature to include. For example, for Loudness, we have the 7 statistical features and 3 variation features. We know we wont be including all, or even more than one, of each of these, so we should start by cutting out the redundant ones.

To do this we need to calculate some sort of simple prediction accuracy metric for each individual feature to the output variable. If output is categorical, I recommend AUC.

Filtering features

max_corr <- function(feature_list, target_variable, data) {
    cor_table <- cor(data[feature_list], data[target_variable])
    max_feature <- rownames(cor_table)[which.max(abs(cor_table))]
    max_value <- cor_table[which.max(abs(cor_table))]
    results <- c(max_feature, max_value)
    results
}
